  "exploit_path": {
    "summary": "The attacker, operating from address 0x0b2bcf06f740c322bc7276b6b90de08812ce9bfe, executed a price manipulation exploit on Arbitrum via transaction 0x6a2f989b5493b52ffc078d0a59a3bf9727d134b403aa6e0bf309fd513a728f7f. Forensic evidence from the DeFiHackLabs proof-of-concept (DeltaPrime_exp.sol) indicates the attack leveraged Balancer Vault (0xBA12222222228d8Ba445958a75a0704d566BF2C8) for flash loan operations, manipulating prices of WETH (0x82aF49447D8a07e3bd95BD0d56f35241523fBab1) and associated tokens. The attack contract was deployed at 0xb87881637b5c8e6885c51ab7d895e53fa7d7c567. The price manipulation technique allowed the attacker to exploit valuation discrepancies within the protocol's lending or trading mechanisms, draining funds through artificially inflated or deflated asset prices.",
